	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><i>I'd have added some more incentive to do Assassinations and Rescues</i><br />
<br />
Point rewards should scale based on the number of attempts or successful completions of a given adventure type.  So that if everyone is doing slaughters, the game tracks that and makes them worth less points and makes an assassination worth more, for instance.<br />
<br />
This dynamic tracking and weighting of rewards would eventually make it worthwhile to move to other adventure types.<br />
<br />
<br />
I do agree that collections aren't that different from a slaughter.  I would have preferred a collection being more of a &quot;locate a given item or (very small single-digit-number) pieces of an item in chests&quot;.  Then you would have a somewhat lighter populated dungeon to compensate for the time spent poking in chests.<br />
<br />
That type of adventure would be more of a &quot;sneaking around the lost dungeon to steal the treasure&quot; rather than a &quot;face the untold hordes of endless enemies&quot; type of deal.<br />
<br />
<br />
I also think there needs to be LDoN raids for the pre-VT crowd, the VT crowd, the Elemental crowd and the Time crowd.  Right now, these are weighted towards the higher end of the scale, when there is a fair bit of competition just behind that.  Compeititon based on time in many cases, which LDoN otherwise solves for single group adventuring.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
