	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>re: Assasinate missions<br />
<br />
 – I’ve read a  few horror stories where invariably one dumbass would pull the Boss mob too soon (ex: before clearing the mobs nearby) and cause a wipe.  <br />
-Often the Boss is at the very end of a very long dungeon, so if DPS is not high, the group is running close to the time limit.  So, if a wipe occurs, they may not have enough time to get back to their corpses and kill the Boss guy before the time expires.<br />
- The Boss that is the target of  Assasination NEVER drops loot, yet every other Named does.  The Boss should drop a piece of loot, or perhaps his head, which could then be turned in at the Wayfarer camp for some sort of bonus <br />
<br />
re: Rescue missions<br />
<br />
- I have read one or two stories of bugginess, such as the NPC being rescued getting stuck in the zone geography and refusing to move forward.  I’d provide links but can’t remember what forum I read this on, lol.   <br />
<br />
<br />
re: collection missions<br />
<br />
- until recently these were very buggy, they seem to be fixed for the most part.<br />
<br />
I also envisioned a ‘find the treasure’ type of mission where you sneak in and steal something…It would be cool if you had to make your way through a dungeon not simply by killing everything (though some killing would be necessary) but  by solving certain ‘puzzles’ (with xp recvd for solving):<br />
<br />
…such as how to get across a chasm to a ledge that leads into a tunnel when spellcasting has been disabled in the area (ex: clicky items might work, so someone with a Pegasus cloak or ring of levitation could get across, and maybe trigger a button that would release a bridge…or a mage with COH could CoH the rest across) (exp awarded as soon as last member of group crosses to other side.)<br />
<br />
…or speaking to a ‘door’ that talks in riddles, you have to guess the riddle (several different ones for different instances) in order to get the door to open.<br />
<br />
…or you have to hunt down 5 chests (guaranteed openable by someone in the group, assuming the casters have the spells – don’t have the spell, don’t take the mission, so if the group only has a rogue, all chests would be pickable, or if there is an INT caster too, one or more might be magic, etc).  Inside the chests are 5 pieces of a whatchamacallit that you have to combine in a container you loot off the boss mob, in order to win.  Partial points awarded for every piece collected before the time limit.  If 40 points = total win, each piece could be = 5 points (collect all 5 pieces = 25 points, nice partial reward, nothing gimp like 2 points for completing after timeframe…)<br />
<br />
As it is now, a collect mission is just an extended slaughter mission.  With a slaughetr mission, if you have to kill 50 baddies, once you kill them, you win.  <br />
<br />
But witha collect mission, if you have to collect 50 thingamadoodles, if the 50 baddies you killed don't each have a thingamadoodle you have to keep killing more baddies until you make up the difference.<br />
<br />
Not a problem if you like to do a clean sweep and so usually stay the extra 30 mins at the end anyways for more xp and sellable loots, but many players like to get in, get the win, and move on to the next adventure.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
