<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="blank">Magelo Profile</a></div>

<div>Join Date: Jun 2003</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Changes I'd make:<br />
<br />
1) Odus theme. Additional ruins of Paineel or (preferably) Lower Warrens.<br />
<br />
2) Paw theme. We don't need so much concentrated on the east coast of Antonica, and Paw gets almost no attention nowadays.<br />
<br />
3) Work the victims into mission objectives.<br />
<br />
4) Work the chests into mission objectives.<br />
<br />
5) More unique models on bosses. There's a good one in Miragul's (the floating guy in the orb of magical energy), but I haven't seen any others.<br />
<br />
6) Make Rujarkan Hills its own zone with its associated camp in the zone.<br />
<br />
7) Positive faction hits. It's ridiculous to do oodles of DGuk missions and to get no faction improvements with live Frogloks or Gukta.<br />
<br />
8) Positive faction with the Wayfarers. They have merchants at each camp. I don't know where this bizarre faction-phobia has come from since PoP, but it's dumb and it's wasting a useful tool in EQ.<br />
<br />
9) Dramatically drop the costs of chest spells. The real reason people don't get these isn't because the chests aren't worth it (I see a lot of people who want to open them, even in pick-up groups), it's because choosing between chest spells and Pack Shrew or chest spells and Ice Meteor, et cetera, is a no brainer. Hell, don't make them cost points at all.<br />
<br />
10) Make interactive objects more common, including outside LDoN. Having to pickpocket furniture in Luclin, for instance, is moronic.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				"It's partly the curiosity, partly a sense of adventure, but mostly I think it's the fame and the money."<br><font size=1><br><a href=http://www.graffe.com/library.php?id=8 target="_blank">Whizbang's Handbook for Young Wizards</a></font>
			</div>
