		<!-- message -->
		<div>I really feel the adventures are too onesided and after a while got really boring. I haven't done any adventures in a while already eventhough there are still some things I'd like to get (few more spells and gear, I already have MM pants with 2 augments, Ice Meteor and the LDoN chest spells).<br />
<br />
For one thing, I don't really see the point of the time limit. It doesn't really seem necessary to me. Sure it can be exciting if you end up having to race against the clock, but that really doesn't happen that much anyway.<br />
<br />
I'd like to see alot more interactivity in the dungeons, I'd love to see something along the lines of this:<br />
<br />
You take a rescue mission, your group fights towards the rescue npc when he/she tells you she won't leave the dungeon without recovering an important artifact first. This in turn requires you to locate a chest with the artifact, and if you don't have any classes that can open it you have to kill a boss to get the key.<br />
<br />
Now *that* sounds like an adventure to me... Twists and turns, unexpected things happening instead of a linear purpose. It could take a while because of this so perhaps get rid of the time limit entirely or make it optional missions and you get extra time if you accept or something. And extra AP if you clear it. Mindless slaughter and the other onesided missions = teh yawn.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
