	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I am still wondering why they decreased the group number minimum from 4 to 3.<br />
I rarely hear of groups of 4 doing adventures, let alone 3 unless they wanted to make things more challenging for players with uber gear and they complained.<br />
<br />
I am what you might consider a &quot;casual&quot; adventurer as I only do a few on the weekends..weeknights are too busy and short for me on EQ. But when I do go the overwhelming attitude of most pick up groups I find myself in is that the preference is for slaughter missions. The reason is obvious to me..we don't know each other and our abilities and most all by now have been in some horrid groups and suffered some nasty adventures. Slaughter missions require less team coordination and is easier for 6 people who don't know each other.<br />
<br />
When they do make changes I hope they keep this in mind..there is a big difference between groups and their make up in classes and abilities and the pros/cons of a pick up group vs. a guild/friend group.<br />
<br />
Someone somewhere has the stats on mission preferences by server and I would be willing to bet that the big majority is slaughter missions..either they make them less attractive to encourage people to try other types or give in and make it easier to select them to begin with.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
